SLS 26RS-3470 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 115
BY SENATOR DUPLESSIS
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates Tuesday, May 12, 2026, as A Day Without
Child Care Day at the Louisiana State Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Tuesday, May 12, 2026, as A Day Without Child Care Day at the Louisiana
3 State Capitol.
4 WHEREAS, early childhood educators make up the workforce that supports the
5 employment of tens of thousands of working Louisiana parents; and
6 WHEREAS, early childhood education, from birth to kindergarten, is significantly
7 underfunded causing educators to leave the field to earn livable wages, resulting in many
8 families unable to access necessary care; and
9 WHEREAS, disruption in child care leaves families, providers, and businesses
10 vulnerable and costs Louisiana's economy one billion three hundred million dollars each
11 year; and
12 WHEREAS, For Providers By Providers (4PXP), Louisiana's only provider-led early
13 care in education (ECE) organization, is leading the statewide coordination of the National
14 Day Without Child Care to elevate the voices of educators, families, and providers; and
15 WHEREAS, for generations, early childhood educators, parents, families, and
16 caregivers have been fighting for equitable access to affordable child care, better pay, and
17 working conditions for providers; and
18 WHEREAS, less than half of child care providers offer staff paid sick days, and
